  "doc_id": "9465",
  "text": "Background PSC is normally associated with UC and ileocolitis in CD. IBD in PSC is considered to be a quiescent disease, and pancolitis occurs often (but not necessarily), with rates varying from 35% to 95%. Both BWI and rectal sparing are observed infrequently. The reported rates of BWI found for PSC-UC vary from 5.0% to 42.9%. In UC without PSC, the involvement of the ileum is not frequent, ranging from 2.5% to 24% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] ].",
